# Web App Development

When working under `web-app/`, follow the web-app-dev skill.

## Required Context

Before implementation or debugging, read:

- `.codebuddy/skills/web-app-dev/SKILL.md`
- `.codebuddy/skills/web-app-dev/reference/architecture.md`
- `.codebuddy/skills/web-app-dev/reference/conventions.md`
- `.codebuddy/skills/web-app-dev/reference/component-catalog.md` when touching components
- `.codebuddy/skills/web-app-dev/reference/gotchas.md` when debugging known issues

## Architecture Rules

- Use Astro for static layout and content rendering.
- Use React Islands only for client-side interaction.
- Keep Markdown content in `Docs/30-tutorials/`; do not copy tutorial content into `web-app/`.
- Keep the app statically buildable; do not introduce SSR or hybrid mode unless explicitly requested.
- Keep terminal integration dev-only and isolated from production builds.
- Prefer existing components and utilities before adding new abstractions.

## Workflow Routing

- New page or feature: read `workflows/implement.md`.
- Bug fix: read `workflows/fix-bug.md`.
- Component work: read `workflows/component.md`.
- Visual-only change: read `workflows/style.md`.
- Refactor or performance work: read `workflows/refactor.md`.
